Key Match Events: Cenk Tosun scored in stoppage time to send Turkey into the knockout stage with a 2-1 win over the Czech Republic.
Czech forward Tomas Chory was shown a red card after a flare-up between players and substitutes.
Czech team captain Tomas Soucek and Turkey's Arda Guler were both shown yellow cards.
Czech midfielder Antonin Barak was sent off in the 20th minute after receiving two yellow cards.
Hakan Calhanoglu broke the deadlock with a low shot inside the far post in the 51st minute.
Czech goalkeeper Jindrich Stanek made a brilliant save but was unable to continue due to a shoulder injury.
Tomas Soucek equalized in the 66th minute after a goalmouth scramble.
Post-Match Reflections: Cenk Tosun expressed his delight with his goal and mentioned that they had discussed the timing beforehand.
Czech coach Ivan Hasek commented on Barak's sadness and self-punishment after being sent off.
Tomas Soucek expressed disappointment over not advancing and mentioned the difficulty of playing with a player less.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Czech Republic finished bottom of Group F behind Georgia, which progressed as one of the best third-place teams.
Turkey finished runner-up with six points and will next face Austria in Leipzig.
